<TITLE> Bangladesh win toss, decide to field </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 17 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh won the toss and decided to field in the second and final Test against West Indies at the National Cricket Stadium in St George's, Grenada on Friday. The Tigers will be led by Shakib Al Hasan in place of injured captain Mashrafe Bin Mortaza. Left-arm spinner Enamul Haque Jr is playing in place of the Bangladesh captain. West Indies made one change with Ryan Hinds replacing Nikita Miller. Bangladesh lead the series 1-0 after winning the first Test at St Vincent by 95 runs on July 13. Teams: Bangladesh: Tamim Iqbal, Junaed Siddique, Imrul Kayes, Mohammad Ashraful, Raqibul Hasan, Shakib Al Hasan (capt), Mushfiqur Rahim (wk), Mahmudullah Riyad, Enamul Haque Jr, Shahadat Hossain, Rubel Hossain. West Indies: DM Richards, OJ Phillips, TM Dowlin, RO Hinds, FL Reifer (capt), DE Bernard, CAK Walton (wk), DJG Sammy, TL Best, RA Austin, KAJ R
